config I2C_MASTER_AXI
	tristate "Custom AXI4-Lite I2C master (i2c_master_axi IP)"
	depends on OF
	depends on I2C
	help
	  Say Y or M here if you want to use the custom i2c_master_axi
	  IP shipped with the I2C_Master_Controller project. The driver
	  exposes a standard Linux i2c_adapter that can host any I2C
	  client (e.g. ssd1306fb-i2c, at24 EEPROM, …).

	  This option only matters when the driver is integrated into
	  the kernel tree (drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig). When built as an
	  out-of-tree module via Buildroot, see
	  buildroot/package/i2c-master-axi/.
